# Important Methods in Wrapper Classes

| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `valueOf()` | Converts primitive/string into wrapper object |
| `parseInt()` | Converts string into integer |
| `parseDouble()` | Converts string into double |
| `toString()` | Converts value into string |
| `intValue()` | Converts object into int |
| `doubleValue()` | Converts object into double |
| `compareTo()` | Compares two wrapper objects |
| `equals()` | Compares values |

---

# 1. valueOf() Method

## Purpose

Converts primitive value into wrapper object.

## Example

```java
class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int num = 50;

        Integer obj = Integer.valueOf(num);

        System.out.println(obj);
    }
}
```

---

# 2. parseInt() Method

## Purpose

Converts string into integer.

## Example

```java
class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String s = "123";

        int num = Integer.parseInt(s);

        System.out.println(num + 10);
    }
}
```

## Output

```java
133
```

---

# 3. toString() Method

## Purpose

Converts value into string.

## Example

```java
class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Integer num = 100;

        String s = num.toString();

        System.out.println(s);
    }
}
```

---

# 4. compareTo() Method

## Purpose

Compares two wrapper objects.

## Example

```java
class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Integer a = 10;
        Integer b = 20;

        System.out.println(a.compareTo(b));
    }
}
```

## Output

```java
-1
```

